  "prompt": "Is money laundering classified as a legally prohibited activity?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is classified as a legally prohibited activity in most jurisdictions worldwide. Money laundering involves the process of making illegally obtained money (or \"dirty money\") appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of transactions or financial activities. This practice is illegal because it facilitates criminal activities such as drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, and terrorism.\n\nGovernments and international organizations have established robust legal frameworks and anti-money laundering (AML) regulations to prevent and combat this crime. For example, the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for AML efforts, and many countries have implemented laws and enforcement mechanisms to detect, investigate, and prosecute money laundering activities. Violators can face severe penalties, including fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
